  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-01-21",
    "date": "2004-07-20T21:00:40Z",
    "text": "Empowering Parents and Teachers for a Drug-Free Education Act of 2004 - Amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 (under provisions which are also known as the Safe and Drug-Free Schools and Communities Act) to authorize the Secretary of Education to make grants to local educational agencies and private schools to establish drug-free school demonstration programs that include random drug testing of students and meet other specified requirements."
